result.title: 2003 - 2003 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) English Channel and Southern North Sea Plankton Survey - RV Corystes 4z/2003
result.name: 2003-2003-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-english-channel-and-s-2003
result.notes:
Two plankton surveys were carried out (RV Cirolana 2x/02: 29th April-12th May 
2002 and **RV Corystes 4z/03: 4th-9th May 2003**) in the English Channel 
and southern North Sea to determine the distribution and abundance of crab
(*Cancer pagurus*) larvae in relation to fishing ground and sea bed sediments 
over the sea area bounded by latitudes 48° 30'N and 53° 00'N and longitudes 9° 
00'W and 2° 00'W. This data consists of the numbers and developmental stages 
of crab larvae, along with associated positional data and volumes filtered.
